post_text:
After much deliberation, and in consultation with local public health officials, school administration has decided to postpone homecoming activities planned for next week. While we truly wanted the students, staff, parents and community members to celebrate homecoming in the typical fashion, it is simply not possible at this time. We must do what we can to mitigate the spread of Covid-19 and protect the health and safety of all stakeholders.

We are working with the student council to reschedule the more traditional activities associated with homecoming this winter or spring. More information regarding the rescheduled homecoming week will be forthcoming. Thank you, in advance, for your support of this decision. Go Mustangs!

post_text:
Congratulations to the 2019-2020 Schrage Award winners: Mackenzie Christian, Luke Johnson, and Blake Gates!

The Schrage Award has been given out since 1990 in memoriam of Sandy Schrage. Sandy was a PE teacher at Independence Middle School many years ago. When she died suddenly in her retirement years, her mom and sister wanted to honor her memory by giving an award in her name.

We honor at least one 8th grade boy and one 8th grade girl each year who exemplify her strength of character and compassion for all she came in contact with. This award is normally given at our 4th quarter assembly, but was moved due to the 2019-2020 school year ending early.

Hey, Mustangs! We need your help:

Our trusty Mustang has been entered in the Healthiest State 10th Annual Walk's School Mascot Challenge. If we win, our district will receive a grand prize of $1,000 to use on health and wellness projects!

The competition will be split into 6 rounds. Each round will begin each Monday at 12 a.m. and end at 11:59 p.m. the following Sunday. The final round will be shorter and end at noon on Wednesday, October 7.

Aug. 31-Sept. 6: Round of 64
Sept. 7-13: Round of 32
Sept. 14-20: Round of 16
Sept. 21-27: Round of 8
Sept. 28-Oct. 4: Final 4
Oct. 4-7: Finals

Use the link below and remember to vote each week! Go Mustangs!

7th Grade Students/Parents/Guardians-

Per the Independence Board of Education recommendation last night, August 17, 2020, all 7th grade students/parents and guardians who are coming to either Welcome Night (Wednesday or Thursday) must wear a mask/face covering upon entering the building and throughout the time in the building.

Also, each student/parent and guardian will have his/her temperature checked upon entering. If a person's temperature is 100.4 or above, he/she will not be able to attend and must leave the building immediately.

Thank you in advance for your cooperation. Go Mustangs!

ATTENTION PARENTS AND FAMILIES:

We will be holding a Zoom meeting TOMORROW, August 18, at 5pm for all families who chose to have their students participate in Remote Learning for the upcoming school year.

A link to the meeting will be sent to the email address you have on file with the school. The meeting will be recorded for those who cannot attend the meeting at 5 p.m.

Please note that if you plan to have your students attend school in-person, you do not need to participate in the meeting.

Call the district office at (319) 334-7400 if you have questions.

Interested in participating in Girls on the Run?

We will be offering a modified 8 week long season starting Sept 14. Practices are at West Elementary on Mon and Thu 3:30 - 5. We do need helpers and one more coach. If anyone is interested in coaching, please contact Jamie Knebel jamie.knebel@yahoo.com. Scholarships are available.

You can register starting Aug 15 and there is a limited number of girls this season. No more than 12 participants are allowed.
http://www.girlsontheruniowa.org

post_text:
The ICSD Hybrid Learning plan has been posted on the Return to Learn page on the district website. Feel free to read through the Hybrid plan and if you have any questions, contact the Central Office at 319-334-7400. The Hybrid plan is one of three plans the district has developed due to the Covid-19 outbreak. At this time the district intends to return to school utilizing the "On-Site" model. The On-Site plan gives parents the option of sending their children to school or the choice of remote learning from their homes Monday - Friday.

The school district will continue to work with Public Health and if a change in the education model is needed, the district will communicate that change.

https://docs.google.com/document/d/16TpETwnvHRTfQq__GsZ_9i64TwQvbKuzQia8sHcNPxo/edit#heading=h.a8w7urq9noj7

After receiving further health guidance, as strictly a precautionary measure to help ensure the health and safety of our players and coaches, HS football camp is cancelled for the rest of the week.

We encourage students to take the necessary precautions and action steps to remain safe and healthy. Official practice, at this time, is scheduled for Monday, August 10th from 4-7:30 p.m. at Lyle Leinbaugh Field. If there are changes to this schedule, for whatever reason, notification will be communicated.

The Independence Community School District Leadership Team has been working diligently on a Return to Learn plan for the ICSD. This is a working plan that will be updated frequently from now until the start of the 2020-2021 school year. A decision about which plan we will return with in the fall will be made by the end of July and communicated out to families, students and staff.
Thank you for your patience with this and understanding that we are trying to keep students and staff safe while still ensuring an education and school experience that is second to none.

You can also find a link to this document on the home page of the district website under the announcement section.

https://docs.google.com/document/d/1HCJr7xUaPPDkuVHkTNvl030SBd9sC_ARoRji4Rzs9UU/edit

The state‚Äôs "Technology Access Survey" will close at 11:59 p.m. on Wednesday, June 24. The following link will direct you to the survey. The survey should take no longer than five minutes to complete and will help the state and us to better understand the specific technology needs of PK-12 and post secondary learners. ‚ùóÔ∏èATTENTION ICSD PARENTS:‚ùóÔ∏è

In preparing for fall registration at Independence, the district has been working to convert all online payments to MySchoolBucks in an effort to make it easier for parents to pay student fees. During this process, MySchoolBucks sent out late payment notifications to those with overdue payments sooner than the district had anticipated. Although the notifications were sent out prematurely, please keep in mind that these payments are still due. If you have questions or need to work out a payment plan please contact Laura Morine at (319) 332-0458.

üéìüéì IMPORTANT NOTE ABOUT GRADUATION:

Class of 2020 and Parents/Guardians-
Please find below general information regarding Commencement 2020. More specific information will be coming next week.

1. Commencement Practice- Thursday, June 25th at 9:00 a.m. Practice is mandatory. Students need to be here at 8:45, so we can start on time.

2. Commencement Ceremony- Sunday, June 28th at 2:00 p.m. Doors open for seating at 1:15 p.m. The building will open at 1. Students must be here by 1:45 p.m.

3. Each student will get 8 tickets for attendees. Only people with tickets will be allowed to attend. All attendees will be seated in the bleachers. All floor seating is reserved for graduates. Seating in the bleachers is on a first come, first serve basis, but attendees must sit every other row to maintain social distancing.

4. Caps and Gowns and tickets will be handed out at rehearsal once all bills are paid and the student has taken the senior exit survey, which was sent today.

Again, more information is forthcoming. We wanted to get this information out today. Thanks! Go Mustangs!

post_text:
IMPORTANT PROM ANNOUNCEMENT
After multiple conversations with Buchanan Public Health officials, input from other local and state health organizations, and guidance from the Iowa Department of Education, the Independence Community School District has decided to cancel Prom 2020. We all know the importance of prom for any high school student, especially seniors and juniors, so please know this was a very difficult decision. In the end, however, administrative personnel did not believe we could meet the current, and future, social distancing requirements to ensure the safety and well-being of our students. Thanks.
Go Mustangs!
text:
IMPORTANT PROM ANNOUNCEMENT
After multiple conversations with Buchanan Public Health officials, input from other local and state health organizations, and guidance from the Iowa Department of Education, the Independence Community School District has decided to cancel Prom 2020. We all know the importance of prom for any high school student, especially seniors and juniors, so please know this was a very difficult decision. In the end, however, administrative personnel did not believe we could meet the current, and future, social distancing requirements to ensure the safety and well-being of our students. Thanks.
Go Mustangs!

Independence Mustang Cross Country - Track and Field
April 29 at 4:38 PM ¬∑

Today we will recognize senior, Michael Higgins. Michael has been on the track team for four years. Each year his times have dropped and he was starting to really take off as a track runner. This year Michael decided he wanted to leave the sprinter group and join the middle distance group. I thought this was a little odd because he had been a sprinter for three years. He joined the middle distance group and was doing an awesome job! I was eager to see how Michael was going to do in his new races! Michael we wish you the best of luck next year in the Iowa National Guard.

Name: Michael Higgins
Parents: Daryl and Alice Higgins
Events: 4x200 and 4x400
Favorite Memories: Every practice we got to run (all practices)
Future Plans: Go to training to become a combat medic for
Iowa National Guard, then go to the University of Iowa
for a pre-med degree and later become a doctor.

Independence Mustang Cross Country - Track and Field
April 28 at 9:24 AM ¬∑

The senior we will recognize today is Kenzie Fischels. Kenzie has been part of the track program for all four years of her HS career. She has scored several points for the team in shot put and discus. My favorite story about Kenzie was when we needed her to run a 4x200 leg for an injured athlete. She was very nervous but when she took off all of us coaches looked at each other. We looked at our watch when she was finished and were shocked! This girl has some speed! Kenzie we wish you the best of luck next year at Kirkwood.

Name: Kenzie Fischels
Parents: Jeff and Kelley Fischels
Events: Discus
Favorite Memories: Winning WaMac in discus at West Delaware and cheering on the 4x400
Future Plans: Attending Kirkwood in the fall for business marketing and management.

‚ùóÔ∏èATTENTION EAST & WEST ELEMENTARY PARENTS‚ùóÔ∏è

Parents-
In response to Governor Reynolds' announcement for schools to remain closed for the rest of the 2019-2020 school year, we would like to offer students the opportunity to check out an electronic device for the remainder of the school year. This would be iPads for grades K-2 and Chromebooks for grades 3-6.

We will have devices prepared for curbside checkout in front of East Elementary from 2:00-6:00 PM, Tuesday April 21, 2020. Administration will be there to get you the devices you need for any students in grades Kindergarten- 6th. We will do our best to make the process as efficient and safe as possible. Administration will be developing a plan next week for families to retrieve any classroom/locker materials left in the building at a later date.

If you have any questions or concerns, please don't hesitate to contact us.

Danielle Donnelly ddonnelly@independence.k12.ia.us East Elementary Principal (K-2)

Cheri Reed creed@independence.k12.ia.us West Elementary Principal (3-6)

post_text:
Dear Students and Families,

As you may have heard, Governor Reynolds announced yesterday that schools in Iowa should remain closed through April 30 in response to the COVID-19 crisis. While we are disappointed knowing that it will be several more weeks before we see our students, the safety of our community and state comes first.

Our board will be meeting on Monday evening to review options outlined by the Iowa Department of Education for continued learning during the closure. We want to ensure that we have the ability to provide learning experiences in a virtual environment and to provide educational opportunities for all of our students.

We know that you have many questions. Rest assured that as soon as we have more specific information about how we will move forward with learning, we will share it with you.

Please don't hesitate to reach out to me if you have any questions.

Best wishes and stay safe,

Russell Reiter

Sign In with Username and Password
Click on Grades and Attendance
Thank you! Go Mustangs!

This week, members of the Independence Community School District have been working at the 2020 IHSAA State Wrestling Championships. Mr. Shannon and Mr. Anderson have been overseeing the head table, while some Independence students have also been working in various roles.

Annabelle Magsamen, Brittney Klever, and Natalee Anderson have been working with the Iowa High School Sports Network (IHSSN), posting videos and photos to IHSSN's social media. Callie Meyer and Sydney Schwartz have been helping out as substitute tableworkers on the floor.

This has been a great experience for everyone involved in helping at arguably the greatest state wrestling tournament in the country. Pictured from left to right are: Mr. Shannon, Annabelle Magsamen, Brittney Klever, Sydney Schwartz, Natalee Anderson, Callie Meyer, and Mr. Anderson.

Vote on March 3rd!

Will it raise my taxes?

No, this will not raise taxes. Approving the Revenue Purpose Statement will allow the district to access future SAVE funds, but it will not change the current sales tax rate. The penny sales tax that funds SAVE will be collected across the state regardless of whether or not this measure is approved. This vote is in regards to how the district utilizes these funds.

For more information please visit:

https://www.independence.k12.ia.us/announcements/vote-on-march-3rd/

Believe it or not, Kindergarten Round-Up is just around the corner!

Join us on Friday, March 20 for one of two sessions: 8:30am to 11:00am OR 12:30pm to 3pm.

Be sure to sign your child up by Wednesday, February 26 by stopping by the Early Childhood Center between 11am and 1pm Monday-Friday or by calling East Elementary at (319) 334-7425.

post_text:
Vote on March 3rd!

Why is it important now?

Independence current Revenue Purpose Statement will expire in 2031. The district is seeking voter approval of a new RPS that would extend for the duration of the penny sales tax (SAVE) which is allowed by Iowa law through the year 2050.

For more information please visit:

https://www.independence.k12.ia.us/announcements/vote-on-march-3rd/

What have Save Funds been used for in the district?

The SAVE revenue has funded many key infrastructure and technology projects in the district, including:

‚ñ™Ô∏èConstruction of the Independence Junior/Senior High School, in conjunction with general obligation bonds
‚ñ™Ô∏èRenovations and additions at West Elementary.
‚ñ™Ô∏èTechnology infrastructure improvements, as well as student and staff technology devices
‚ñ™Ô∏èBuses and other transportation needs
‚ñ™Ô∏èRoof repairs to school facilities

post_text:
Attention Parents!!!!
Gov. Reynolds has launched a new youth vaping awareness and prevention campaign. This campaign is designed to raise awareness among teenagers and their parents around the risks of youth vaping, which is a growing epidemic in Iowa and nationally.

The ICSD Nursing Department would like to share the following information with you to help you start a conversation with your child/children.

https://www.independence.k12.ia.us/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/OSH-E-Cigarettes-and-Youth-What-Parents-Need-to-Know-20190327-508.pdf
